00:29:54.560 --> 00:29:57.619 align:middle line:84%
very good ways, and sound
ways, to think about ourselves

00:29:57.619 --> 00:29:58.535 align:middle line:90%
and our relationship--

00:29:58.535 --> 00:29:59.519 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Choices, yes.

00:29:59.519 --> 00:30:00.560 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: --to the world.

00:30:00.560 --> 00:30:01.770 align:middle line:84%
They may not use
the same language,

00:30:01.770 --> 00:30:02.830 align:middle line:84%
but this is what
we're all doing.

00:30:02.830 --> 00:30:04.621 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It' all the
same information, yeah.

00:30:04.621 --> 00:30:06.965 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I realized
early in my life

00:30:06.965 --> 00:30:09.590 align:middle line:84%
as an engineer-- I was actually
working in the defense industry

00:30:09.590 --> 00:30:11.610 align:middle line:84%
during the last years
of the Cold War, Lisa.

00:30:11.610 --> 00:30:13.790 align:middle line:84%
A very frightening
time in the history

00:30:13.790 --> 00:30:19.700 align:middle line:84%
of the world behind the scenes,
when the world came unthinkably

00:30:19.700 --> 00:30:22.950 align:middle line:84%
close to doing the unthinkable
and unleashing nuclear weapons

00:30:22.950 --> 00:30:24.340 align:middle line:90%
on civilian populations.

00:30:24.340 --> 00:30:27.680 align:middle line:84%
And it was at that time that I
began to ask myself, who am I?

00:30:27.680 --> 00:30:28.732 align:middle line:90%
Who are we?

00:30:28.732 --> 00:30:30.190 align:middle line:84%
And I realized the
only way I would

00:30:30.190 --> 00:30:32.490 align:middle line:84%
find that answer
was to go to some

00:30:32.490 --> 00:30:37.490 align:middle line:84%
of the most isolated,
magnificent, remote, beautiful

00:30:37.490 --> 00:30:40.330 align:middle line:84%
places remaining on the Earth,
where that information is more

00:30:40.330 --> 00:30:40.830 align:middle line:90%
intact.

00:30:40.830 --> 00:30:43.930 align:middle line:84%
It hasn't been disturbed by
a modern way of thinking.

00:30:43.930 --> 00:30:46.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you were a part
of building those systems,

00:30:46.500 --> 00:30:47.420 align:middle line:90%
and you had--

00:30:47.420 --> 00:30:49.190 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I worked in a
nuclear weapons program called

00:30:49.190 --> 00:30:51.405 align:middle line:84%
the Peacekeeper Missile during
the last years of the Cold--

00:30:51.405 --> 00:30:52.405 align:middle line:90%
the Peacekeeper Missile.

00:30:52.405 --> 00:30:53.822 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The name,
the Peacekeeper.

00:30:53.822 --> 00:30:55.613 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: There's a
whole different program

00:30:55.613 --> 00:30:56.680 align:middle line:90%
we could do with that.

00:30:56.680 --> 00:30:59.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You had a whole,
complete awakening around that,

00:30:59.150 --> 00:30:59.650 align:middle line:90%
didn't you?

00:30:59.650 --> 00:31:01.260 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: What I came
to understand is this--

00:31:01.260 --> 00:31:03.009 align:middle line:84%
and I'll just share
it with our listeners.

00:31:03.009 --> 00:31:04.720 align:middle line:90%
It's a story I share seldom.

00:31:04.720 --> 00:31:07.372 align:middle line:84%
But we're talking about it
here and I'm happy to do it.

00:31:07.372 --> 00:31:09.830 align:middle line:84%
It was a very frightening time
in the history of our world.

00:31:09.830 --> 00:31:11.780 align:middle line:84%
And I was asking
myself, of all people,

00:31:11.780 --> 00:31:15.380 align:middle line:84%
why am I working behind the
scenes on a weapons project

00:31:15.380 --> 00:31:18.500 align:middle line:84%
that I have such
emotions around?

00:31:18.500 --> 00:31:20.350 align:middle line:84%
And I asked myself
the question, what

00:31:20.350 --> 00:31:25.560 align:middle line:84%
would happen if we married
the wisdom of 5,000

00:31:25.560 --> 00:31:30.330 align:middle line:84%
years of human history-- what
we've learned in 5,000 years--

00:31:30.330 --> 00:31:32.840 align:middle line:84%
if we married that ancient
wisdom with the best

00:31:32.840 --> 00:31:33.820 align:middle line:90%
science of today.

00:31:33.820 --> 00:31:37.150 align:middle line:84%
What if we weaved those two
ways of knowing into a greater

00:31:37.150 --> 00:31:40.940 align:middle line:84%
understanding that would help
us prevent the kinds of wars

00:31:40.940 --> 00:31:43.920 align:middle line:84%
that I was in the process
of working in the industry

00:31:43.920 --> 00:31:44.794 align:middle line:90%
to support?

00:31:44.794 --> 00:31:45.710 align:middle line:90%
Where would that lead?

00:31:45.710 --> 00:31:46.829 align:middle line:90%
The answer to that.

00:31:46.829 --> 00:31:48.620 align:middle line:84%
If you're looking on
your screen right now,

00:31:48.620 --> 00:31:50.740 align:middle line:90%
you're seeing a collage of me.

00:31:50.740 --> 00:31:53.120 align:middle line:90%
Those are all of my images.

00:31:53.120 --> 00:31:56.540 align:middle line:84%
People have called
to my attention

00:31:56.540 --> 00:31:59.800 align:middle line:84%
that my search to
understand our relationship

00:31:59.800 --> 00:32:01.650 align:middle line:84%
to the world in these
traditions is actually

00:32:01.650 --> 00:32:04.490 align:middle line:84%
documented by the length of
my hair over the years, Lisa,

00:32:04.490 --> 00:32:06.795 align:middle line:90%
and by the color of my hair.

00:32:06.795 --> 00:32:09.230 align:middle line:84%
But my journey has
taken me into some

00:32:09.230 --> 00:32:10.980 align:middle line:90%
