modern human was not, in fact,

00:49:49.950 --> 00:49:51.490 align:middle line:90%
descended from Neanderthals."

00:49:51.490 --> 00:49:54.670 align:middle line:84%
And since that time, 40
more Neanderthal bodies

00:49:54.670 --> 00:49:55.420 align:middle line:90%
have been found.

00:49:55.420 --> 00:49:58.250 align:middle line:84%
And the DNA has supported
this conclusion.

00:49:58.250 --> 00:49:59.690 align:middle line:90%
So now we know who we're not.

00:49:59.690 --> 00:50:01.570 align:middle line:84%
We are not descended
from Neanderthal.

00:50:01.570 --> 00:50:05.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Why isn't
this more mainstream?

00:50:05.170 --> 00:50:07.560 align:middle line:84%
Why hasn't this turned
science on its head?

00:50:07.560 --> 00:50:08.984 align:middle line:90%
This was in 2000.

00:50:08.984 --> 00:50:10.900 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: One of the
reasons, in all fairness,

00:50:10.900 --> 00:50:13.730 align:middle line:84%
it takes a long time
for new discoveries

00:50:13.730 --> 00:50:16.870 align:middle line:84%
to trickle down into what's
commonly accepted in the world.

00:50:16.870 --> 00:50:18.680 align:middle line:84%
That would be
important any time.

00:50:18.680 --> 00:50:22.900 align:middle line:84%
Right now, we're being told we
don't have decades to do this.

00:50:22.900 --> 00:50:25.420 align:middle line:84%
We've got to redefine our
relationship to the world.

00:50:25.420 --> 00:50:27.150 align:middle line:84%
And this is just
one small piece.

00:50:27.150 --> 00:50:29.622 align:middle line:84%
But we're going to go somewhere
with this very quickly.

00:50:29.622 --> 00:50:30.705 align:middle line:90%
But we know who we're not.

00:50:30.705 --> 00:50:32.371 align:middle line:84%
We're not descendants
from Neanderthals.

00:50:32.371 --> 00:50:34.940 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, we walked
the Earth with Neanderthal.

00:50:34.940 --> 00:50:36.150 align:middle line:84%
If we shared the
Earth with them,

00:50:36.150 --> 00:50:37.733 align:middle line:84%
we could not have
descended from them.

00:50:37.733 --> 00:50:40.000 align:middle line:84%
That now is scientific
fact and we know that.

00:50:40.000 --> 00:50:43.920 align:middle line:84%
So here's another
graph on your screen.

00:50:43.920 --> 00:50:46.380 align:middle line:84%
We are in the center
at the very top.

00:50:46.380 --> 00:50:49.370 align:middle line:84%
And what we know is that the
form of modern human as we

00:50:49.370 --> 00:50:52.020 align:middle line:84%
are today, we appeared
relatively suddenly

00:50:52.020 --> 00:50:53.677 align:middle line:90%
about 200,000 years ago.

00:50:53.677 --> 00:50:55.010 align:middle line:90%
We used to be called Cro-Magnon.

00:50:55.010 --> 00:50:57.510 align:middle line:84%
And now we are called
anatomically modern human

00:50:57.510 --> 00:50:58.200 align:middle line:90%
because we are.

00:50:58.200 --> 00:50:59.710 align:middle line:90%
That describes us.

00:50:59.710 --> 00:51:02.080 align:middle line:84%
We haven't changed,
Lisa, in 200,000 years.

00:51:02.080 --> 00:51:03.049 align:middle line:90%
This is the thing.

00:51:03.049 --> 00:51:05.090 align:middle line:84%
If you take their skeleton
and put it next to you

00:51:05.090 --> 00:51:06.927 align:middle line:84%
and me, except for
thicker leg bones,

00:51:06.927 --> 00:51:08.760 align:middle line:84%
for all intents and
purposes we're the same.

00:51:08.760 --> 00:51:10.800 align:middle line:90%
That is not Darwinian evolution.

00:51:10.800 --> 00:51:12.917 align:middle line:84%
We don't know
where we came from.

00:51:12.917 --> 00:51:14.750 align:middle line:84%
But if we want to get
to the bottom of this,

00:51:14.750 --> 00:51:18.050 align:middle line:84%
we've got to understand what
happened 200,000 years ago.

00:51:18.050 --> 00:51:19.050 align:middle line:90%
I don't know the answer.

00:51:19.050 --> 00:51:21.620 align:middle line:84%
But I know that the
Darwinian theory of evolution

00:51:21.620 --> 00:51:22.620 align:middle line:90%
is not explaining it.

00:51:22.620 --> 00:51:26.450 align:middle line:84%
And the new theories are being
discouraged or, in some cases,

00:51:26.450 --> 00:51:28.450 align:middle line:90%
not even allowed to be shared.

00:51:28.450 --> 00:51:30.484 align:middle line:84%
So we have a whole
generation of young people

00:51:30.484 --> 00:51:32.400 align:middle line:84%
that want to dedicate
their lives to answering

00:51:32.400 --> 00:51:34.490 align:middle line:84%
the great questions
of our existence.

00:51:34.490 --> 00:51:37.550 align:middle line:84%
They're being required to do
so within a limited framework

00:51:37.550 --> 00:51:39.710 align:middle line:84%
of what we already know
as obsolete science.

00:51:39.710 --> 00:51:42.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So where are
we going with this?

00:51:42.130 --> 00:51:44.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we don't know
where we come from.

00:51:44.220 --> 00:51:45.741 align:middle line:90%
This is still the missing link.

00:51:45.741 --> 00:51:46.740 align:middle line:90%
It's still undetermined.

00:51:46.740 --> 00:51:47.660 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: I think DNA is
going to tell the story.

00:51:47.660 --> 00:51:47.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Eventually.

00:51:47.930 --> 00:51:50.060 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: Rather than a
family tree, my sense,

00:51:50.060 --> 00:51:51.560 align:middle line:84%
my Greggism sense,
is that we're not

00:51:51.560 --> 00:51:52.726 align:middle line:90%
going to have a family tree.

00:51:52.726 --> 00:51:54.290 align:middle line:90%
I think we have a family bush.

00:51:54.290 --> 00:51:56.250 align:middle line:84%
It's a very small
bush and we're it.

00:51:56.250 --> 00:51:59.180 align:middle line:84%
I think that we are
our own species.

00:51:59.180 --> 00:52:01.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Derived from where?

00:52:01.000 --> 00:52:04.470 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: In the book I talk
about some of the DNA studies.

00:52:04.470 --> 00:52:06.950 align:middle line:84%
And what scientists are
saying-- geneticists publish

00:52:06.950 --> 00:52:11.050 align:middle line:84%
this in genetics journals-- are
saying that specifically human

00:52:11.050 --> 00:52:13.310 align:middle line:84%
chromosome number
two, that allows

00:52:13.310 --> 00:52:15.940 align:middle line:84%
us to be so much of
who we are, could not

00:52:15.940 --> 00:52:18.910 align:middle line:84%
have happened by natural
evolutionary processes.

00:52:18.910 --> 00:52:23.340 align:middle line:84%
That something happened to fuse
the genes in the way that they

00:52:23.340 --> 00:52:26.520 align:middle line:84%
are that cannot be
explained by natural terms.

00:52:26.520 --> 00:52:27.520 align:middle line:90%
They have to stop there.

00:52:27.520 --> 00:52:29.130 align:middle line:84%
They can't go any
further because they

00:52:29.130 --> 00:52:30.640 align:middle line:90%
don't know what else to say.

00:52:30.640 --> 00:52:32.580 align:middle line:84%
They're saying,
factually, it could not

00:52:32.580 --> 00:52:36.400 align:middle line:84%
have happened through
evolutionary processes.

00:52:36.400 --> 00:52:37.880 align:middle line:90%
And there's a lot more to this.

00:52:37.880 --> 00:52:40.040 align:middle line:84%
In the interest of time, we're
going through this quickly.

00:52:40.040 --> 00:52:41.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This is a whole, right,
subject within itself, yes.

00:52:41.900 --> 00:52:43.524 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: But, here's
what Darwin said.

00:52:43.524 --> 00:52:45.575 align:middle line:84%
He expected his ideas
would be overturned.

00:52:45.575 --> 00:52:47.640 align:middle line:84%
He said, "If it
could be demonstrated

00:52:47.640 --> 00:52:51.660 align:middle line:84%
that any complex organ existed
which could not possibly

00:52:51.660 --> 00:52:55.280 align:middle line:84%
have been formed by
numerous, successive, slight

00:52:55.280 --> 00:52:57.480 align:middle line:84%
modifications," he
says, "my theory

00:52:57.480 --> 00:52:58.740 align:middle line:90%
would absolutely break down."

00:52:58.740 --> 00:53:00.920 align:middle line:84%
And we haven't even
talked about DNA yet.

00:53:00.920 --> 00:53:01.900 align:middle line:90%
DNA chain.

00:53:01.900 --> 00:53:03.740 align:middle line:84%
Darwin could not
possibly have known

00:53:03.740 --> 00:53:06.720 align:middle line:84%
in his time about the cells
and the DNA like we do in ours.

00:53:06.720 --> 00:53:08.700 align:middle line:84%
He expected his ideas
to be overturned.

00:53:08.700 --> 00:53:12.529 align:middle line:84%
And it's not being allowed in
mainstream media, academia,

00:53:12.529 --> 00:53:14.320 align:middle line:84%
classrooms, textbooks,
and teachings today.

00:53:14.320 --> 00:53:15.736 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's not
being challenged.

00:53:15.736 --> 00:53:17.520 align:middle line:90%
It's being presented as fact.

00:53:17.520 --> 00:53:18.020 align:middle line:90%
As history.

00:53:18.020 --> 00:53:20.680 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: And any alternative
or competing theories

00:53:20.680 --> 00:53:22.929 align:middle line:84%
that suggest something
else are not being allowed.

00:53:22.929 --> 00:53:24.720 align:middle line:84%
Now, I think that's
the problem, because we

00:53:24.720 --> 00:53:28.290 align:middle line:84%
have brilliant minds, beautiful
hearts of a whole generation

00:53:28.290 --> 00:53:30.956 align:middle line:84%
of young people, that are
about to be unleashed to answer

00:53:30.956 --> 00:53:32.580 align:middle line:84%
the deepest questions
of our existence.

00:53:32.580 --> 00:53:33.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That are asking.

00:53:33.330 --> 00:53:34.390 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: And they're
being required

00:53:34.390 --> 00:53:36.764 align:middle line:84%
to do so within the limited
parameters of what we already

00:53:36.764 --> 00:53:38.370 align:middle line:84%
know is a false and
obsolete science.

00:53:38.370 --> 00:53:39.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's why
this program exists.

00:53:39.500 --> 00:53:39.980 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: Deep truth.

00:53:39.980 --> 00:53:42.396 align:middle line:84%
This is our first deep truth,
beyond any reasonable doubt.

00:53:42.396 --> 00:53:44.880 align:middle line:84%
Evolution doesn't
describe and explain

00:53:44.880 --> 00:53:46.620 align:middle line:90%
life itself or human life.

00:53:46.620 --> 00:53:50.190 align:middle line:84%
But this leads to the
second Darwinian concept

00:53:50.190 --> 00:53:52.610 align:middle line:84%
that I believe is
wreaking the greatest

00:53:52.610 --> 00:53:54.510 align:middle line:84%
havoc upon our lives
and our world today.

00:53:54.510 --> 00:53:56.710 align:middle line:84%
From your family dinner
tables to the collapse

00:53:56.710 --> 00:54:00.550 align:middle line:84%
of the global economic system,
I think it's based in this idea.

00:54:00.550 --> 00:54:04.530 align:middle line:84%
Darwin believed that when
he looked into nature,

00:54:04.530 --> 00:54:07.430 align:middle line:84%
and he saw the way
certain insects or animals

00:54:07.430 --> 00:54:10.410 align:middle line:84%
behaved in one location,
that he was looking

00:54:10.410 --> 00:54:15.190 align:middle line:84%
at small expressions in that
place of a greater law that

00:54:15.190 --> 00:54:18.360 align:middle line:84%
applied to every
life everywhere.

00:54:18.360 --> 00:54:22.100 align:middle line:84%
So for example, he said-- and
I love it when he does this.

00:54:22.100 --> 00:54:23.990 align:middle line:84%
He starts this
explanation by saying

00:54:23.990 --> 00:54:26.170 align:middle line:84%
it may not be logical
to think this way.

00:54:26.170 --> 00:54:28.479 align:middle line:84%
So even he's got a question
while he's saying it.

00:54:28.479 --> 00:54:29.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's a qualifier.

00:54:29.520 --> 00:54:30.070 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: This is a quote.

00:54:30.070 --> 00:54:32.300 align:middle line:84%
He says, "it may not
be a logical deduction.

00:54:32.300 --> 00:54:35.320 align:middle line:84%
But to my imagination,"
Darwin says,

00:54:35.320 --> 00:54:38.660 align:middle line:84%
"it's far more satisfactory
to look at these competing

00:54:38.660 --> 00:54:43.230 align:middle line:84%
instincts, such as young birds
ejecting their foster brothers

00:54:43.230 --> 00:54:44.654 align:middle line:90%
or sisters from the nest."

00:54:44.654 --> 00:54:45.570 align:middle line:90%
Two birds in the nest.

00:54:45.570 --> 00:54:46.890 align:middle line:84%
Another bird comes
that's different.

00:54:46.890 --> 00:54:48.473 align:middle line:84%
And they eject it
and leave it to die.

00:54:48.473 --> 00:54:50.770 align:middle line:84%
Or ants making slaves
out of other ants

00:54:50.770 --> 00:54:53.020 align:middle line:84%
because they are more
powerful and they can.

00:54:53.020 --> 00:54:57.740 align:middle line:84%
He says he is looking at these
"as small consequences of one

00:54:57.740 --> 00:55:00.320 align:middle line:84%
general law leading to the
advancement of all beings

00:55:00.320 --> 00:55:01.140 align:middle line:90%
everywhere.

00:55:01.140 --> 00:55:05.070 align:middle line:84%
That law is multiply, very,
let the strongest live,

00:55:05.070 --> 00:55:06.250 align:middle line:90%
and the weakest die."

00:55:06.250 --> 00:55:09.980 align:middle line:84%
Let the strongest live
and the weakest die.

00:55:09.980 --> 00:55:14.057 align:middle line:84%
This is such a
dangerous way to think.

00:55:14.057 --> 00:55:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And if you're wondering
how dangerous,

00:55:15.640 --> 00:55:18.140 align:middle line:84%
you look at the consequences
of this in the world around us.

00:55:18.140 --> 00:55:21.639 align:middle line:84%
Our corporate systems are
based upon the competition,

00:55:21.639 --> 00:55:23.430 align:middle line:84%
let the strongest live
and the weakest die.

00:55:23.430 --> 00:55:26.370 align:middle line:84%
The economic system that is
breaking and wreaking havoc

00:55:26.370 --> 00:55:28.870 align:middle line:84%
and causing suffering
throughout the world.

00:55:28.870 --> 00:55:32.690 align:middle line:84%
The way that we are dealing
with diminishing resources,

00:55:32.690 --> 00:55:35.380 align:middle line:84%
how we share them and
how we help one another,

00:55:35.380 --> 00:55:37.600 align:middle line:90%
all based upon these ideas.

00:55:37.600 --> 00:55:40.746 align:middle line:84%
We have just emerged
from the 20th century.

00:55:40.746 --> 00:55:43.380 align:middle line:84%
If you think about what we
were talking about here,

00:55:43.380 --> 00:55:44.910 align:middle line:90%
this was 1859.

00:55:44.910 --> 00:55:49.270 align:middle line:84%
The modern world is largely
based upon Darwinian ideas.

00:55:49.270 --> 00:55:52.420 align:middle line:84%
Some of the most
distorted and twisted acts

00:55:52.420 --> 00:55:54.980 align:middle line:84%
of atrocity of
human against human

00:55:54.980 --> 00:55:56.641 align:middle line:90%
occurred in the 20th century.

00:55:56.641 --> 00:55:58.640 align:middle line:84%
We don't even have to go
into what all they are.

00:55:58.640 --> 00:56:00.960 align:middle line:84%
Our listeners know
and our viewers know.

00:56:00.960 --> 00:56:02.760 align:middle line:84%
But many of them were
justified, they said,

00:56:02.760 --> 00:56:05.250 align:middle line:84%
because Darwin based
this in science,

00:56:05.250 --> 00:56:11.290 align:middle line:84%
it must be OK for us to treat
our fellow humans the way

00:56:11.290 --> 00:56:13.020 align:middle line:90%
that we're treating them.

00:56:13.020 --> 00:56:14.640 align:middle line:84%
Or in some cases,
exterminate them.

00:56:14.640 --> 00:56:17.170 align:middle line:84%
Let the strongest live
and the weakest die.

00:56:17.170 --> 00:56:20.190 align:middle line:84%
We're seeing the way we
deal with climate change.

00:56:20.190 --> 00:56:22.730 align:middle line:84%
We're seeing it as a
competitive battle that

00:56:22.730 --> 00:56:24.620 align:middle line:84%
must be won rather
than something that we

00:56:24.620 --> 00:56:26.880 align:middle line:90%
adapt to as a natural change.

00:56:26.880 --> 00:56:29.644 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this was just a
small part of what Darwin said.

00:56:29.644 --> 00:56:30.310 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: It is.

00:56:30.310 --> 00:56:31.090 align:middle line:90%
It's a small part.

00:56:31.090 --> 00:56:34.622 align:middle line:84%
But it became a very powerful,
dominant part of the teaching.

00:56:34.622 --> 00:56:35.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of our culture.

00:56:35.580 --> 00:56:37.340 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: And it is
deeply entrenched

00:56:37.340 --> 00:56:38.660 align:middle line:90%
into our world today.

00:56:38.660 --> 00:56:40.510 align:middle line:84%
And this is just part
of the deep truths.

00:56:40.510 --> 00:56:41.280 align:middle line:90%
Now the good news.

00:56:41.280 --> 00:56:43.230 align:middle line:84%
Let's go to the good news,
because there is good news.

00:56:43.230 --> 00:56:43.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Thank you.

00:56:43.770 --> 00:56:44.770 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: The good news.

00:56:44.770 --> 00:56:47.920 align:middle line:84%
In the late 20th, now
early 20th century--

00:56:47.920 --> 00:56:51.750 align:middle line:84%
21st century, over 400
peer-reviewed studies

00:56:51.750 --> 00:56:54.300 align:middle line:84%
asked a single question--
what's the optimum amount

00:56:54.300 --> 00:56:56.960 align:middle line:84%
of competition in the
classroom, in the workplace,

00:56:56.960 --> 00:56:58.110 align:middle line:90%
on the playing field?

00:56:58.110 --> 00:57:01.850 align:middle line:84%
Violent competition, not a
friendly game of checkers.

00:57:01.850 --> 00:57:04.570 align:middle line:84%
All 400 studies came back
with the same answer.

00:57:04.570 --> 00:57:06.760 align:middle line:84%
Alfie Khan, in his book,
"No Contest-- The Case

00:57:06.760 --> 00:57:08.540 align:middle line:84%
Against Competition,"
described this.

00:57:08.540 --> 00:57:10.140 align:middle line:84%
This is a quote.
"The ideal amount

00:57:10.140 --> 00:57:12.462 align:middle line:84%
of competition in
any environment,

00:57:12.462 --> 00:57:13.920 align:middle line:84%
in the classroom,
in the workplace,

00:57:13.920 --> 00:57:15.669 align:middle line:84%
in the family, the
playing field, is none.

00:57:15.669 --> 00:57:19.730 align:middle line:84%
Competition always, always,
always is destructive."

00:57:19.730 --> 00:57:22.740 align:middle line:84%
That is followed by
a very prestigious--

00:57:22.740 --> 00:57:26.180 align:middle line:84%
an article in a very prestigious
journal, "New Scientist."

00:57:26.180 --> 00:57:29.314 align:middle line:84%
Michael Le Page,
this was in 2008.

00:57:29.314 --> 00:57:29.980 align:middle line:90%
This is a quote.

00:57:29.980 --> 00:57:31.780 align:middle line:84%
He said, "What we
see in the wild

00:57:31.780 --> 00:57:34.054 align:middle line:90%
is not every animal for itself."

00:57:34.054 --> 00:57:36.470 align:middle line:84%
That's very different than
what we've been led to believe.

00:57:36.470 --> 00:57:38.011 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, what
Darwin said, yeah.

00:57:38.011 --> 00:57:41.320 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: He said, "Cooperation
is an incredibly successful

00:57:41.320 --> 00:57:42.270 align:middle line:90%
survival strategy.

00:57:42.270 --> 00:57:44.870 align:middle line:84%
In fact, when
cooperation breaks down,

00:57:44.870 --> 00:57:47.170 align:middle line:84%
the results can
become disastrous."

00:57:47.170 --> 00:57:49.640 align:middle line:84%
If you're wondering
where you can

00:57:49.640 --> 00:57:52.040 align:middle line:84%
see a good example
of cooperation,

00:57:52.040 --> 00:57:54.350 align:middle line:84%
you need look no further
than the body that

00:57:54.350 --> 00:57:57.480 align:middle line:84%
houses the soul that is
watching this program.

00:57:57.480 --> 00:58:00.900 align:middle line:84%
Because your body is made up
of over 50 trillion cells.

00:58:00.900 --> 00:58:02.990 align:middle line:84%
And those cells
must cooperatively

00:58:02.990 --> 00:58:08.220 align:middle line:84%
work together in a very precise
way to allow you your life.

00:58:08.220 --> 00:58:09.940 align:middle line:84%
And when that
cooperation breaks down,

00:58:09.940 --> 00:58:11.369 align:middle line:90%
the results are disastrous.

00:58:11.369 --> 00:58:12.910 align:middle line:84%
This is one of the
beautiful examples

00:58:12.910 --> 00:58:15.517 align:middle line:84%
in nature of where
cooperation is so vital.

00:58:15.517 --> 00:58:16.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's true.

00:58:16.350 --> 00:58:19.090 align:middle line:84%
Our bodies always have an
innate ability to heal itself.

00:58:19.090 --> 00:58:23.070 align:middle line:84%
That is, it's always
attempting its highest order

00:58:23.070 --> 00:58:25.184 align:middle line:84%
to achieve coherence
within the body.

00:58:25.184 --> 00:58:27.100 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: And we're just
touching the surface.

00:58:27.100 --> 00:58:28.391 align:middle line:90%
This is the tip of the iceberg.

00:58:28.391 --> 00:58:30.840 align:middle line:84%
But we're doing this,
Lisa, to get somewhere.

00:58:30.840 --> 00:58:33.980 align:middle line:84%
To share with our
viewers that not all

00:58:33.980 --> 00:58:36.180 align:middle line:84%
of the truths that we've
been led to believe

00:58:36.180 --> 00:58:38.190 align:middle line:90%
are actually truths.

00:58:38.190 --> 00:58:39.750 align:middle line:84%
And the science is
overturning them.

00:58:39.750 --> 00:58:42.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I mean, this might
be a psychology question,

00:58:42.210 --> 00:58:45.470 align:middle line:84%
but isn't the human psyche
hardwired for competition?

00:58:45.470 --> 00:58:48.350 align:middle line:84%
I know that-- Is it really
all based on this scientific--

00:58:48.350 --> 00:58:50.058 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: We're
hardwired for excellence.

00:58:50.058 --> 00:58:51.157 align:middle line:90%
We want to do well.

00:58:51.157 --> 00:58:53.740 align:middle line:84%
And what you're going to see--
and this will take us into this

00:58:53.740 --> 00:58:57.470 align:middle line:84%
next section very quickly
because violent competition

00:58:57.470 --> 00:59:00.990 align:middle line:84%
among people, that we have
been led to believe is actually

00:59:00.990 --> 00:59:03.920 align:middle line:84%
fundamental in human
nature, interestingly,

00:59:03.920 --> 00:59:07.060 align:middle line:84%
we do not see the evidence of
it in the archaeological record

00:59:07.060 --> 00:59:10.640 align:middle line:84%
in the 5,000-year cycle
that proceeds this cycle.

00:59:10.640 --> 00:59:14.570 align:middle line:84%
It's only this 5,000-year
cycle where we see the evidence

00:59:14.570 --> 00:59:18.100 align:middle line:84%
