circular plazas.

01:02:47.360 --> 01:02:49.480 align:middle line:84%
A mysterious advanced
civilization.

01:02:49.480 --> 01:02:51.170 align:middle line:84%
We don't know where
they came from.

01:02:51.170 --> 01:02:54.990 align:middle line:84%
When I was there, the dates
actually came in for this site.

01:02:54.990 --> 01:02:58.800 align:middle line:84%
This that you're looking at is
actually an aerial view of one

01:02:58.800 --> 01:03:00.160 align:middle line:90%
of these sites.

01:03:00.160 --> 01:03:02.730 align:middle line:90%
The site is called Caral, Peru.

01:03:02.730 --> 01:03:03.540 align:middle line:90%
The date came in.

01:03:03.540 --> 01:03:05.373 align:middle line:84%
And remember, we're
taught that civilization

01:03:05.373 --> 01:03:08.860 align:middle line:84%
began in a primitive
state 5,500 years ago.

01:03:08.860 --> 01:03:12.640 align:middle line:84%
This site collapsed when
we're told civilization began.

01:03:12.640 --> 01:03:16.470 align:middle line:84%
This advanced site is at least
7,000 years old and collapsed

01:03:16.470 --> 01:03:19.120 align:middle line:84%
2,000 years later
around 5,000 years ago.

01:03:19.120 --> 01:03:23.410 align:middle line:84%
It's now dated between 7,000
and 5,000 years before present.

01:03:23.410 --> 01:03:25.580 align:middle line:84%
This now is the oldest
site in all the Americas.

01:03:25.580 --> 01:03:27.947 align:middle line:84%
Older than the Inca, than
the Aztec, than the Maya.

01:03:27.947 --> 01:03:29.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This site in Peru.

01:03:29.030 --> 01:03:29.930 align:middle line:90%
>>BRADEN: In Peru.

01:03:29.930 --> 01:03:31.900 align:middle line:84%
And it's rewriting
the history books.

01:03:31.900 --> 01:03:32.859 align:middle line:90%
But it's only one site.

01:03:32.859 --> 01:03:35.233 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to cut the
chase and go to the oldest site

01:03:35.233 --> 01:03:35.920 align:middle line:90%
everywhere.

01:03:35.920 --> 01:03:37.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wait, wait.

01:03:37.370 --> 01:03:38.590 align:middle line:90%
I just have to ask.

01:03:38.590 --> 01:03:42.100 align:middle line:84%
You're there in Peru
when that data came in?

01:03:42.100 --> 01:03:44.070 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: There's a whole
story I could share.

01:03:44.070 --> 01:03:45.500 align:middle line:90%
And how are we doing on time?

01:03:45.500 --> 01:03:46.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What did you do?

01:03:46.700 --> 01:03:47.670 align:middle line:90%
We have time.

01:03:47.670 --> 01:03:48.960 align:middle line:90%
Go for it.

01:03:48.960 --> 01:03:52.490 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: The day that I
was here with our guide

01:03:52.490 --> 01:03:56.670 align:middle line:84%
in this very isolated,
remote, colorless land, where

01:03:56.670 --> 01:03:58.410 align:middle line:84%
