relieved because I

01:05:00.580 --> 01:05:02.790 align:middle line:84%
had a sense what
I was seeing here.

01:05:02.790 --> 01:05:05.090 align:middle line:84%
And the archaeologist
that I was talking to,

01:05:05.090 --> 01:05:07.360 align:middle line:84%
he wanted to tell me
what had been found.

01:05:07.360 --> 01:05:09.360 align:middle line:84%
I was frustrating him
with the questions

01:05:09.360 --> 01:05:11.190 align:middle line:84%
that I was asking that
he couldn't answer.

01:05:11.190 --> 01:05:11.949 align:middle line:90%
Who built it?

01:05:11.949 --> 01:05:12.990 align:middle line:90%
Where did they come from?

01:05:12.990 --> 01:05:14.060 align:middle line:90%
Where are the bodies?

01:05:14.060 --> 01:05:15.610 align:middle line:90%
Are there any weapons?

01:05:15.610 --> 01:05:18.130 align:middle line:90%
No walls fortifying this area.

01:05:18.130 --> 01:05:19.277 align:middle line:90%
Who were these people?

01:05:19.277 --> 01:05:20.235 align:middle line:90%
And he couldn't answer.

01:05:20.235 --> 01:05:23.240 align:middle line:84%
And he says, we don't know
the answer to those questions.

01:05:23.240 --> 01:05:25.550 align:middle line:84%
But there's a mathematics,
there's an architecture,

01:05:25.550 --> 01:05:27.130 align:middle line:90%
there's a way of agriculture.

01:05:27.130 --> 01:05:30.760 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, astronomical markers
very apparent that are here.

01:05:30.760 --> 01:05:32.200 align:middle line:84%
This was an advanced
civilization.

01:05:32.200 --> 01:05:34.540 align:middle line:84%
These people knew
things that we're only

01:05:34.540 --> 01:05:35.630 align:middle line:90%
beginning to understand.

01:05:35.630 --> 01:05:37.880 align:middle line:84%
And they helped to
understand the bridge.

01:05:37.880 --> 01:05:40.736 align:middle line:84%
When we see the Maya,
for example, and we say,

01:05:40.736 --> 01:05:41.610 align:middle line:90%
how did they do this?

01:05:41.610 --> 01:05:42.701 align:middle line:90%
Where did they come from?

01:05:42.701 --> 01:05:43.325 align:middle line:90%
Out of nowhere?

01:05:43.325 --> 01:05:44.366 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't out of nowhere.

01:05:44.366 --> 01:05:46.370 align:middle line:84%
They were bridged from
other civilizations

01:05:46.370 --> 01:05:48.475 align:middle line:84%
that we simply are not
aware of and are only now

01:05:48.475 --> 01:05:50.030 align:middle line:90%
are becoming aware of.

01:05:50.030 --> 01:05:54.430 align:middle line:84%
So this is the value of
going to a place like this.

01:05:54.430 --> 01:05:56.490 align:middle line:90%
The oldest site in the world.

01:05:56.490 --> 01:05:58.460 align:middle line:84%
Now, there may be
others that are older.

01:05:58.460 --> 01:06:00.340 align:middle line:84%
But this is the
oldest scientifically

01:06:00.340 --> 01:06:03.690 align:middle line:84%
dated, peer-reviewed
and accepted dated site

01:06:03.690 --> 01:06:05.070 align:middle line:90%
in the world now is in Turkey.

01:06:05.070 --> 01:06:07.790 align:middle line:84%
It's a place called
Gobekli Tepe, Turkey.

01:06:07.790 --> 01:06:09.610 align:middle line:90%
This is an amazing site.

01:06:09.610 --> 01:06:13.958 align:middle line:84%
It was rediscovered by a
German archaeologist in 2004.

